long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1220034 Debug log from kst2 (menu Help-> Debug dialog)
Description of problem: kst2 starts, but there is no possibility to load any csv dataset.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): Kst 2.0.8
How reproducible: Always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Install kst-2.0.8-9.fc24.x86_64 with or without it's additional kst-*-2.0.8-9.fc24.x86_64 packages. 2. Start kst2 application. 3. Try to open any dataset file. 4. Click Help-> Debug window
Actual results: Impossible to load dataset file.
Expected results: Load dataset from file.
Additional info:
Debug log in attachment suggests that kst packages need to be recompiled with gcc 6 key.
Local compilation works but packaged doesn't.
Problem appeared just after gcc upgrade from 4 to 6.
kst-2.0.8-11.fc24 has been submitted as an update to Fedora 24. https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2016-4cef6c27a3

kst-2.0.8-11.fc24 has been pushed to the Fedora 24 testing repository. If problems still persist, please make note of it in this bug report. See https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/QA:Updates_Testing for instructions on how to install test updates. You can provide feedback for this update here: https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2016-4cef6c27a3
In my case updated version of package works very well. Thank you very much.
kst-2.0.8-11.fc24 has been pushed to the Fedora 24 stable repository. If problems still persist, please make note of it in this bug report.
